DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the principle that values passed as arguments to custom hooks should be treated as immutable. Directly mutating hook arguments (`icon.className = computeStyle(icon, theme);`) is incorrect and can lead to unexpected behavior, especially with memoization. The correct approach is to create a copy of the argument (`{ ...icon }`) before making modifications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/reference/rules/components-and-hooks-must-be-pure.md#_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
function useIconStyle(icon) {
  const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
  if (icon.enabled) {
    icon.className = computeStyle(icon, theme); // 🔴 Bad: never mutate hook arguments directly
  }
  return icon;
}
```

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
function useIconStyle(icon) {
  const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
  const newIcon = { ...icon }; // ✅ Good: make a copy instead
  if (newIcon.enabled) {
    newIcon.className = computeStyle(newIcon, theme);
  }
  return newIcon;
}
```

