TITLE: Custom useFadeIn Hook (JS Class Integration)
DESCRIPTION: A custom React hook that uses the `useEffect` hook to manage the lifecycle of a `FadeInAnimation` class instance. It connects the React component's ref and duration prop to the imperative animation logic encapsulated in the class.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md#_snippet_60

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { FadeInAnimation } from './animation.js';

export function useFadeIn(ref, duration) {
  useEffect(() => {
    const animation = new FadeInAnimation(ref.current);
    animation.start(duration);
    return () => {
      animation.stop();
    };
  }, [ref, duration]);
}
```

