TITLE: Initial useCounter Hook (Fixed Delay)
DESCRIPTION: The initial implementation of the useCounter hook with a hardcoded interval delay of 1000ms. This version does not accept a delay parameter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/reusing-logic-with-custom-hooks.md#_snippet_69

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export function useCounter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  useEffect(() => {
    const id = setInterval(() => {
      setCount(c => c + 1);
    }, 1000);
    return () => clearInterval(id);
  }, []);
  return count;
}
```

